ABUJA â€“ Dr Ogbonnaya Onu, Minister of Science and Technology, has described the establishment of the University of Transportation in Daura, Katsina State by the present administration as a triumph of the Executive Order 5 initiated by the Ministry. Speaking on the sideline of the conference of Nigerian Society of Engineers (NSE) on Tuesday in Kano, Onu said the University would pave way for the domestication of railway engineering and general transportation sciences in Nigeria, thereby bridging the technology and skill gap in the railway and transportation sector. He said the ground-breaking ceremony of the University of Transportation showed the commitment of the Federal Government to strengthen the role of Science, Technology and Innovation in line with Executive Order 5. The minister quoted Mr President as saying that the project was part of the on-going effort of the Federal Government towards promotion and development of indigenous capacity through technology acquisition and knowledge transfer to effectively maintain and operate numerous railway infrastructures. Onu commended President Buhari for placing a premium on the use of indigenous professionals, adding that the development was a good example of local content development in contracts involving science, engineering and technology as enshrined in the Presidential Executive Order 5.